# module: eng.case
# status: supported-sample-row-artifact-seed; planned native runner
# purpose: per-case manifests for sample-to-run workflows.
#
# Current implementation:
#   promoted sample tables with case_id columns produce
#   typed_payload.case_manifests[] entries with case_id, sample row number,
#   source row, deterministic sample row hash, and duplicate/missing case_id
#   status. Native apply/run/collect, case directories, process bindings,
#   resume/cache status, and generated-output linkage remain planned. Workflow
#   examples still use explicit external case_manifest.json files, generated
#   files, process results, and output manifests.
#
# Planned CaseManifest fields:
#   case_id
#   sample row hash
#   case directory
#   generated input files
#   process command and status
#   result files
#   metrics
#   failure reason
#   cache/resume status
#
# Non-goal:
#   loops that mutate files without a case manifest should not become the
#   preferred batch-workflow pattern.
